b'@AnyBodyCanFly Hard to imagine a real asset like real estate won\xe2\x80\x99t continue to go up over the long term (20-30 years)

If you cash flow from it, who cares about short term volatility

Digital transformation like $OPEN and $RDFN may make the housing market even more liquid'

b'Without AI, Zillow, OpenDoor, Redfin, and other tech real estate startups focused on house flipping will continue to burn cash on these deals.

Many of the profitable home flippers have a keen eye when finding properties to flip. AI can give them that perspective.

$OPEN $RDFN'

b'They also provide mortgages and refinancing to home buyers and current homeowners.

They even have a concierge service to help sellers make their home(s) attractive to buyers.

This company is looking to become a real estate disruptive thanks to technology.

$RDFN'

b'They are a real estate brokerage that is known to sell homes faster than the industry average.

And with their move into house flipping, compared to OpenDoor $OPEN and Zillow $Z $ZG, Redfin has been slow to capitalize on the market.

$RDFN'

b'By charging a listing fee based on the value of the home (with each market having a different minimum listing fee) Redfin is making it cheaper for sellers to sell their homes.

And they even provide other ways of savings to both buyers and sellers.

$RDFN'

b'Redfin is disrupting the real estate brokerage industry by charging lower commissions than its competitors.

Many will say that Redfin is like Amazon, where they\xe2\x80\x99re in the business of providing the same product at a lower price.

$RDFN'
